Package de.gematik.bbriccs.fhir.coding

Interface WithStructureDefinition<T extends ProfileVersion>

Type Parameters:
T - is the type of the corresponding version of the profile to which this StructureDefinition belongs
All Superinterfaces:
WithSystem
All Known Implementing Classes:
DeBasisProfilStructDef, HL7StructDef
public interface WithStructureDefinition<T extends ProfileVersion> extends WithSystem
This interface encapsulates the handling of StructureDefinitions for specific profiles and their corresponding versions.

  • Method Details

    • getVersionedUrl

      default String getVersionedUrl(T version)
      Returns the canonical URL of the StructureDefinition with the given version appended to it.

      Example usage: 

      
 // where GKV_WOP is an instance of WithStructureDefinition and has a canonical URL of
 // "http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop"
 DeBasisProfilStructDef.GKV_WOP.getVersionedUrl(DeBasisProfilVersion.V1_4_0);

 // will create the following versioned URL
 http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop|1.4
      Parameters:
      version - the version to append to the canonical URL
      Returns:
      the canonical URL of the StructureDefinition with the given version appended to it

    • asCanonicalType

      default org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.CanonicalType asCanonicalType()
      This method creates a CanonicalType object for this StructureDefinition without any version.

      Example usage: 

      
 // where GKV_WOP is an instance of WithStructureDefinition and has a canonical URL of
 // "http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop"
 val canonical = DeBasisProfilStructDef.GKV_WOP.asCanonicalType();
 resource.getMeta().setProfile(List.of(canonical));

 // will create the following Meta object as the profile definition of a resource
 <meta>
   <profile value="http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop"/>
 </meta>
      Returns:
      the canonical type for this StructureDefinition

    • asCanonicalType

      default org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.CanonicalType asCanonicalType(T version)
      This method creates a CanonicalType object for this StructureDefinition with a specific version.

      Example usage: 

      
 // where GKV_WOP is an instance of WithStructureDefinition and has a canonical URL of
 // "http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop"
 val canonical = DeBasisProfilStructDef.GKV_WOP.asCanonicalType(DeBasisProfilVersion.V1_4_0);
 resource.getMeta().setProfile(List.of(canonical));

 // will create the following Meta object as the profile definition of a resource
 <meta>
   <profile value="http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop|1.4"/>
 </meta>
      Parameters:
      version - to use for the canonical type
      Returns:
      the canonical type for this StructureDefinition

    • asBooleanExtension

      default org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Extension asBooleanExtension(boolean value)
      This method creates an Extension object for this StructureDefinition that contains the provided Code, encoded as a BooleanType as its value.

      Example usage: 

      
 // where GKV_WOP is an instance of WithStructureDefinition and has a canonical URL of
 // "http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop""
 DeBasisProfilStructDef.GKV_WOP.asBooleanExtension(true)

 // will create the following extension when serialized to XML:
 <extension url="http://fhir.de/StructureDefinition/gkv/wop">
   <valueBoolean value="true"/>
 </extension>
      Parameters:
      value - the Code to be encoded as the value of the Extension as a BooleanType
      Returns:
      an Extension object of this StructureDefinition containing the encoded Code as a BooleanType.
      See Also:
      • FHIR DataTypes Boolean

    • asUrlExtension

      default org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Extension asUrlExtension(String url)
      This method creates an Extension object for this StructureDefinition that contains the provided URL, encoded as a UrlType as its value.

      Example usage: 

      
 // where DEEP_LINK is an instance of WithStructureDefinition and has a canonical URL of
 // "https://gematik.de/fhir/erp/StructureDefinition/GEM_ERP_EX_DeepLink"
 ErpWorkflowStructDef.DEEP_LINK.asUrlExtension("https://www.my.diga.app.com/123123");

 // will create the following extension when serialized to XML:
 <extension url="https://gematik.de/fhir/erp/StructureDefinition/GEM_ERP_EX_DeepLink">
   <valueUrl value="https://www.my.diga.app.com/123123"/>
 </extension>
      Parameters:
      url - the URL to be encoded as the value of the Extension
      Returns:
      an Extension object of this StructureDefinition containing the encoded URL as a UrlType.
      See Also:
      • FHIR DataTypes URL
      • RFC 1738

    • asUriExtension

      default org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Extension asUriExtension(String uri)
      This method creates an Extension object for this StructureDefinition that contains the provided URI, encoded as a UriType as its value. The created Extension will have this StructureDefinition's System as its system

      Example usage: 

      
 // where DEEP_LINK is an instance of WithStructureDefinition and has a canonical URL of
 // "https://gematik.de/fhir/erp/StructureDefinition/GEM_ERP_EX_DeepLink"
 ErpWorkflowStructDef.DEEP_LINK.asUrlExtension("https://www.my.diga.app.com/123123");

 // will create the following extension when serialized to XML:
 <extension url="https://gematik.de/fhir/erp/StructureDefinition/GEM_ERP_EX_DeepLink">
   <valueUri value="https://www.my.diga.app.com/123123"/>
 </extension>
      Parameters:
      uri - the URI to be encoded as the value of the Extension
      Returns:
      an Extension object of this StructureDefinition containing the encoded URI as a UriType.
      See Also:
      • FHIR DataTypes URI
      • RFC 3986
